    • Method Detail

      • onPublish

        void onPublish​(MkvObject object,
               boolean start,
               boolean dwl)
        Event generated when a publication becomes available or unavailable.

        It is not safe, publishing new object during this notification.

        Parameters:
        object - the MkvObject representing the publication.
        start - true if the publication is added, false if it is under deletion
        dwl - true if the publication is part of a block of publications (a publish idle event will follow)

      • onPublishIdle

        void onPublishIdle​(String component,
                   boolean start)
        Function called after a block of publications (download) is sent.
        Parameters:
        component - the component name that sent the block of publications
        start - true if the publication were added, false if it were under deletion

      • onSubscribe

        void onSubscribe​(MkvObject obj)
        Function called when an object (record or chain) published by this application is subscribed.
        Parameters:
        obj - the MkvObject.
